contentheadline.headline: International English Speakers' Association of Finland

contentrichtext.text: {{Orphan|date=February 2009}} The '''International English Speakers' Association of Finland''' or more known by its [[abbreviation]] IESAF, is an independent voluntary organisation of [[expatriate|ex-pat]]s and enthusiasts of [[Finland]]. They run [[meetings]] for people who want to live and work in the country, to get around the complex world of the Finnish [[bureaucracy]], assistance with learning the [[Finnish language|Finnish]] language & the local [[convention (norm)|custom]]s and with meeting other ex-pats. ==Websites== [http://www.iesaf.fi IESAF website] [[Category:Organisations based in Finland]] [[Category:Languages of Finland]] [[Category:English language]]
